    "biography": "<p>A wight is an undead spirit that inhabits the body of a deceased human or demihuman. It resembles its living form but appears bone-white and emaciated, with hollow, lifeless eyes. Its burial garments are typically tattered and filthy.</p><p>Wights can only be harmed by silvered or magical weapons. They are greatly feared due to their ability to drain life energy with each strike. Each successful hit drains one level of experience or Hit Die from the victim. Any individual completely drained of life energy by a wight will transform into a wight themselves within 1d4 days and will be under the control of the slayer.</p><p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Barren Lands, Ruins.</p>",
